Question on referencing dynamic content (from a dynamic hubDB based page) in JS. I'm attempting to inject html content after a page event and needing to that content to include dynamic content from the page. I've seen it said that it CAN be done... but I seem to be missing something on how to actually make it happy. For the sake of an example here is this:

```
// this stuff lives in the JS portion of a custom module 

{% if dynamic_page_hubdb_row %}  // do I need to reference the dynamic nature of this here?
  const name = {{dynamic_page_hubdb_row.asset_name}};
  console.log(name);
{% endif %}```

Anybody have some insight on this?
